<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
Worker. Length 2 1/2 - 3 1/2 lines.-Chestnut-brown: closely resembling 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:34391" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyergus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyergus rufescens (Latreille)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">Polyergus rufescens</taxonomicName>
, but with the mandibles toothed; head subovate; the eyes ovate, placed high on the sides of the head towards the vertex. Thorax rounded in front, compressed behind; the metathorax obliquely truncated. Abdomen oblong-ovate, the apex fuscous; the scale of the peduncle incrassate, slightly rounded in front and flattened behind.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
